<subSubSection id="C3126501D816FF993CB4FF6E30FAFA61" pageId="67" pageNumber="1026" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD816FF993CB4FF6E30FAFA61" blockId="67.[151,1058,211,263]" pageId="67" pageNumber="1026">
D i a g n o s i s: The broad testaceous line on the elytral disc will distinguish the members of this species from others within 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D816FF993E70FF4B30FEFA61" box="[595,705,241,263]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="1028" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Peloniinae">Peloniinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3126501D816FF993CB4FEAD305DF952" pageId="67" pageNumber="1026" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD816FF993CB4FEAD305DF952" blockId="67.[151,1059,278,564]" pageId="67" pageNumber="1026">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 6.0 mm; width 2.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD816FF993F5CFEAC31EBFA4A" box="[895,980,278,300]" captionStart="Figs 358-361" captionStartId="117.[151,191,1517,1539]" captionTargetBox="[153,1061,197,1502]" captionTargetId="figure@117.[153,1061,197,1502]" captionTargetPageId="117" captionText="Figs 358-361: Habitus; (358) Alariuscareoritus; (359) Ordinistaxis; (360) Peloniumatrigonatium; (361) Cregyaentrerios." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746842" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746842/files/figure.png" pageId="67" pageNumber="1026">Fig. 359</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium bicolorous, lower frons testaceous, upper frons briefly testaceous, then divided by black triangular black marking, sides of epicranium and cranial venter testaceous; antenna black; pterothorax and abdomen piceous; elytra dark brown, with two testaceous vertical lines, epipleural margin partially testaceous. Head: Eyes large, coarsely facetted, eye wider than frons (EW/FW 33/10); antenna capitate (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD816FF993EF6FE13311FFAD9" box="[725,800,425,447]" captionStart="Figs 43-60" captionStartId="72.[151,191,1361,1383]" captionTargetBox="[157,1053,222,1351]" captionTargetId="figure@72.[152,1057,206,1351]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="Figs 43-60: Antennae; (43) Ordinis taxis; (44) Pelonium tayrona; (45) Neorthopleura turnbowi, male; (46) N. turnbowi, female; (47) Megaphloeus imparilus; (48) Plocamocera catalexis; (48 a) Cregya entrerios; (49) Ridica merida. (50) Kataspinula puebla. (51) Cregya tobagoensis; (52) Topainca patchacutii; (53) Eurycaulis anaxeis; (54) Amboakis expandosa. (55) Ridica achira. (56) Ampleris cacuminis; (57) Sicamus suprus; (58) Sirpa latiflava; (59) Alarius careoritus; (60) Cregya petalosa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746750/files/figure.png" pageId="67" pageNumber="1026">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
), funicular antennomeres widened laterally, capitular antennomeres 8 and 9 rectangular, antennomere 10 oblong. Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD816FF993D46FE593381FA9F" box="[357,446,483,505]" captionStart="Figs 118-133" captionStartId="76.[151,191,1373,1395]" captionTargetBox="[152,1050,202,1340]" captionTargetId="figure@76.[152,1056,202,1357]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="Figs 118-133: Pronota; (118) Pujoliclerus abditus; (119) Nelsopelonium aspikelum; (120) Parapelonides naranjo; (121) Pujoliclerus lasiosus; (122) Neorthopleura rubra; (123) Pujoliclerus ariquemes; (124) Ichnea cerinis; (125) Ampleris amazon; (126) Pujoliclerus abditus; (127) P. dexsus; (128) Sirpa acara; (129) Madoniella aspera; (130) Pelonium tayrona; (131) Megatrachys irrasis; (132) Ordinis taxis; (133) Pujoliclerus cnecostus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746758" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746758/files/figure.png" pageId="67" pageNumber="1026">Fig. 132</figureCitation>
) oblong; lateral tubercles slightly defined (PW/PL 73/80), disc finely punctate; elytral disc with asetiferous punctures (EL/EW 260/70). Abdomen: Pygidium scutiform; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD816FF993E24FDA4305DF952" box="[519,610,542,564]" captionStart="Figs 255-261" captionStartId="92.[151,191,1238,1260]" captionTargetBox="[153,1061,200,1225]" captionTargetId="figure@92.[153,1061,200,1225]" captionTargetPageId="92" captionText="Figs 255-261: Aedeagi; (255) Pujoliclerus tuxtlas; (256) Sicamus suprus; (257) Sirpa acara; (258) Sirpa latiflava; (259) Topainca pachacutii; (260) Pelonium atrigonatium; (261) Ordinis taxis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746790/files/figure.png" pageId="67" pageNumber="1026">Fig. 261.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
